channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Alabama Passes Law Protecting Gun Owners From De Facto Private Sector Firearm Registry
‘Enough’: Controversial ID program for illegal immigrants targeted by GOP senator
item.description: Sen. Josh Hawley is introducing legislation to block a controversial ICE ID program for illegal immigrants -- as it is set to roll out this summer.

item.description: Dr. Ben Carson, who has been mentioned as a potential running mate for presumptive Republican presidential candidate Donald Trump, called for a federal ban on abortion,

Biden rolls out new China tariffs, vows US will ‘never allow’ Beijing to ‘unfairly control’ EV market
item.description: President Biden has announced that his administration is deploying new tariffs against China in sectors including electric vehicles, steel and semiconductors.

item.title: Scimeca: Time for CFPB to Get Out of Consumers' Way
item.description: The CFPB has abandoned consumer interests for an ideological agenda that serves no one. People need access to credit now more than ever.

Biden doesn't support 'full-term' abortion stance pushed by RFK Jr, campaign says
item.description: President Biden's re-election campaign said Tuesday that the president does not support full-term abortions, drawing contrast between remarks made recently by Robert F Kennedy Jr.

item.title: Trump's NYC Trial Slammed by 4 Allies as 'Sham'
item.description: Four of former President Donald Trump's allies attended his business records trial in New York City Tuesday, telling the press during a break that the proceedings are a sham.

item.title: David Hogg Moans About Housing Costs, Scott Presler and Others School Him on Reality of Liberal Choices

item.title: House to Vote on Condemning Biden on Israel Aid
item.description: The House will vote Wednesday on whether to condemn President Joe Biden for pausing arms transfers to Israel.

item.title: Outside the Trump Trial in Manhattan: The Trump Vice Presidential Sweepstakes
Mudslinging candidates in heated House race face voters on big primary day
item.description: Voters will determine the Republican nominee in a heated race for Congress in West Virginia that's seen the top two candidates lob major attacks at one another.

item.title: States Sue Over EEOC Policy on Transgender Workers
item.description: A group of Republican-led U.S. states filed a lawsuit seeking to block the U.S. Equal Employment Opportunity Commission from enforcing broad legal protections for transgender workers.
